## How does Northbeam's ML attribution work?

Northbeam's ML assigns fractional credit to touchpoints, ensuring total attributed conversions sum to exactly 100% of actual sales. When your ad platforms collectively claim 190 conversions for 100 real sales, Northbeam reconciles to reality.

This is different from traditional MTA (first-touch, last-touch, linear) where models can show different totals. Northbeam gives you one reconciled answer. The tradeoff: it's a black box — you trust the ML, or you don't.

