### 1. Triple Whale — Shopify-First ($129-549/mo)

Triple Whale starts cheaper than Northbeam with deep Shopify integration, AI recommendations (Moby), and RFM audiences. GMV-based pricing means costs scale with revenue.

**Why consider over Northbeam:** Cheaper at lower revenue levels. Better Shopify integration. AI recommendations included. Free tier available.

**Why stick with Northbeam:** Northbeam's ML prevents overcounting (more rigorous). Creative analytics are deeper. Better for brands spending $5M+/year on ads where accuracy justifies the price.

Read more: [Triple Whale Pricing](/articles/triple-whale-pricing)

### 2. Cometly — Ad Optimization (~$500/mo)

Cometly specializes in ad platform optimization with strong CAPI enrichment and AI recommendations. Ad-spend-based pricing.

**Why consider over Northbeam:** Cheaper entry point. Better CAPI enrichment for Meta. AI Ads Manager for campaign recommendations. No-code setup.

**Why stick with Northbeam:** Northbeam's ML attribution is more sophisticated. Creative analytics are stronger. MMM+ provides budget allocation that Cometly doesn't offer.

Read more: [Cometly Pricing](/articles/cometly-pricing)

### 3. mbuzz — Flat Pricing at $29-299/mo

mbuzz offers 7 attribution models with custom rules and server-side tracking. Flat tiers — price doesn't scale with pageviews, GMV, or ad spend. *Full disclosure: mbuzz is our product.*

| mbuzz Tier | Price | Records |
|------------|-------|---------|
| Free | $0 | <%= free_event_limit_display %> |
| Starter | $29/mo | 1M |
| Growth | $99/mo | 5M |
| Pro | $299/mo | 25M |

**Why consider over Northbeam:** 3-10x cheaper. Free tier available. 7 transparent models you can inspect (vs Northbeam's ML black box). Custom attribution rules. Server-side tracking.

**Why stick with Northbeam:** Northbeam's ML prevents overcounting. Creative analytics included at Professional tier. Deeper ad platform partnerships (Meta, TikTok, Snap, Pinterest). Purpose-built for enterprise DTC.

### 4. Hyros — High-Ticket Attribution (~$199/mo)

Hyros specializes in high-ticket products and info products with call tracking and long cookie windows.

**Why consider over Northbeam:** Much cheaper. Better for high-ticket ($500+) products. Call tracking included.

**Why stick with Northbeam:** Northbeam is better for standard e-commerce with high SKU counts and lower AOV. ML attribution is more sophisticated.

### 5. GA4 — Free

Google Analytics 4 offers free basic attribution. Not a Northbeam replacement, but a starting point.

**Why consider over Northbeam:** Free. Immediate setup. Good enough for pre-revenue or early-stage brands.

**Why stick with Northbeam:** GA4 has no ML attribution, no creative analytics, no MMM, and overcounts conversions across platforms.

